sabina

Class QueryParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • sabina.QueryParams

  • public class QueryParams
extends java.lang.Object
    This objects represent the parameters sent on a Http Request. Parses parameters keys like in Sinatra. For a querystring like: user[name]=federico&user[lastname]=dayan We get would get a structure like: user : {name: federico, lastname: dayan} That is: queryParamsMapInstance.get("user).get("name").value(); queryParamsMapInstance.get("user).get("lastname").value(); It is null safe, meaning that if a key does not exist, it does not throw NullPointerException, it just returns null.

        public QueryParams get(java.lang.String... keys)
        Returns and element from the specified key.
        For querystring:

        user[name]=fede get("user").get("name").value() # fede or get("user","name").value() # fede
        Parameters:
